FIFA President Gianni Infantino has conveyed a message of condolences to Former UEFA President Lennart Johansson’s family following his passing. Lennart, who headed UEFA from 1990 to 2007 and is famous for having founded the Uefa Champions League, died after a short illness at the age of 89. “I am heartbroken by the news of the passing away of Lennart Johansson,” Infantino said in a statement. “He was a friend and an invaluable source of wisdom and inspiration. “I will be forever grateful for having had him as the president of UEFA when I joined the organisation in 2000. Since then, Lennart has always been a role model of professionalism and, more importantly, of humanity.” 